## What is covered by tests

| Area | Coverage |
| --- | --- |
| Public API | Root vs advanced entrypoint surface checks. |
| Shader pipeline | Source generation and line/source mapping. |
| Uniform system | Type validation, layout, and packing behavior. |
| Material system | Defines/includes/signature/material validation behavior. |
| Texture system | Normalization, URL loader, cancellation, cache behavior. |
| Scheduler | Ordering, invalidation, modes, profiling, diagnostics. |
| Render graph | Validation and execution planning rules. |
| Error system | Error normalization and report shape behavior. |

## Important contracts enforced by tests

| Contract | Expectation |
| --- | --- |
| `FragCanvas` diagnostics | Readable WebGPU errors + `onError` delivery. |
| Hook context safety | `useMotionGPU` and `useFrame` require `FragCanvas` subtree. |
| User context conflicts | `useMotionGPUUserContext` supports `skip`, `merge`, `replace`. |
| Shader pass contract | `ShaderPass` requires `fn shade(inputColor: vec4f, uv: vec2f) -> vec4f`. |

## Build and validation commands

From `packages/motion-gpu`:

```bash
bun run build
bun run test
bun run check
bun run lint
```

## Internal implementation details worth knowing

| Area | Detail |
| --- | --- |
| Uniform writes | Frame uniforms are written each frame; material uniforms use dirty-range updates. |
| Texture fallback | 1x1 fallback textures are used until real source is available. |
| Render target allocation | Reallocation occurs only on signature-changing topology/size/format changes. |
| Shader diagnostics | Compile failures map back to fragment/include/define source references. |
| Scheduler timing | Diagnostics and profiling share same timing collection path. |

## Practical caveats

| Caveat | Guidance |
| --- | --- |
| WebGPU availability | Depends on browser, platform, and secure context. |
| `onInvalidate` vs `perFrame` | Choose explicitly; behavior is materially different. |
| `autoRender = false` | Overrides mode and suppresses all rendering. |
| Material construction | Always use `defineMaterial`; do not handcraft plain material objects. |
